<TITLE> Barapukuria miners resume work </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)The Barapukuria coal mine workers rejoined work on Sunday after calling a strike three days back demanding pay hike M Qamruzzaman, managing director, Barapukuria Coal Mining Company Limited, told bdnews24.com that BCMCL, Chinese contractor's firm XMC and representatives of Barapukuria Coal Mine Workers Rights and Movement Committee at a meeting from 6:30pm on Saturday to 1:30am on Sunday reached an understanding. The meeting accepted and agreed to implement the workers' bonus enhancement right away and assured workers that all of their demands would be met in phases gradually, when the workers agreed to end their strike. The committee convenor Robiul Islam and adviser SM Nuruzzaman said the workers have ceased their strike and resumed work at 7am. About 1,000 workers employed at the coal mine went on a wildcat strike on Thursday midnight demanding realisation of their 14-point charter of demands including increased pay and bonuses. Coal extraction remained suspended during the strike. The other demands include Bengali doctors for the mining workers, extended treatment facilities with 24-hour ambulance service, proper and full treatment of injured workers with full salaries, introduction of food rationing, priority on experience while recruiting new workers, new ID cards to all workers after proper verification. bdnews
